This is a collection of the legal and personal papers of Charles Collins Sr. and
                    Charles Collins Jr. Materials include: warrants; indentures and agreements;
                    records of court costs; receipts for household goods and services; bank checks;
                    and is an 1841-1842 scrapbook of newspaper clippings of poetry, anecdotes, and
                    reports of social and political events. The collection also includes receipts of
                    Daniel Sinclair and some of the firm of D. Sinclair and J.C. Hinchman.
